# =============================================================================
# LiteSpeed / cPanel Passenger — copy to `.htaccess` in THIS directory
# (same folder as passenger_wsgi.py) OR follow your host's doc if it must live
# under public_html instead. Replace ALL placeholders with your real paths.
# =============================================================================
#
# ---- Make http(s)://b.novacarrentals.com/ work (fixes common errors) ----
#
# 1) WSGI vs ASGI: Passenger calls WSGI (environ, start_response).
#    If the panel uses FastAPI `app`, you get:
#      TypeError: FastAPI.__call__() missing ... 'send'
#    Fix: Startup file MUST be passenger_wsgi.py OR wsgi.py from this repo.
#         Application / callable / entry MUST be exactly: application
#         (Accepted aliases: wsgi, wsgi_application — NOT `app`.)
#
# 2) `pip install -r requirements.txt` in THIS domain's venv (needs a2wsgi).
#
# 3) CORS log spam: Older copies of server.py logged a CORS hint at INFO.
#    Deploy the current backend and restart the Passenger app — that message
#    no longer exists. For strict production CORS, set in `.env`:
#      CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-admin-host.com
#    (comma-separated list; omit *.)
#
# 4) LSAPI_CHILDREN / “Reached max children process limit” — not fixable here.
#    In LiteSpeed WebAdmin (or hosting support): Configuration → tuning /
#    external apps → raise LSAPI_CHILDREN (and/or Passenger pool limits) when
#    every worker is busy. Otherwise increase plan or lighten slow requests.
#

PassengerEnabled On
PassengerAppType wsgi
PassengerStartupFile passenger_wsgi.py
PassengerAppRoot "/home/USERNAME/domains/b.novacarrentals.com/backend"
PassengerBaseURI /
PassengerPython "/home/USERNAME/virtualenv/b.novacarrentals.com/3.11/bin/python"

# If the panel ignores the Python path line, set the version only in Setup Python App UI.
# Startup file MUST match the file uploaded (often `passenger_wsgi.py`); if UI asks for an
# “Application root file”, still point it at passenger_wsgi.py and callable `application`.

# Optional: quieter errors in production once everything works:
# PassengerFriendlyErrorPages Off
